OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782895707
OL,3,CRape victim says she 'will never be
OL,4,Cthe same' ahead of sentence review
OL,6,FOne of two girls raped by teenage boys
OL,7,Fin Fordingbridge has said she does not
OL,8,Fthink she "will ever be the same".
OL,10,FJazmine - not her real name - said
OL,11,Fthat the trial of her attackers "broke
OL,12,Fsomething inside me".
OL,14,FIt comes as the Court of Appeal is set
OL,15,Fto decide whether the boys' non-
OL,16,Fcustodial sentences are "unduly
OL,17,Flenient".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782895707
OL,3,CRape victim says she 'will never be
OL,4,Cthe same' ahead of sentence review
OL,6,FJazmine said she feels like she has
OL,7,Fbeen "carrying what happened every
OL,8,Fday" since she was attacked by two
OL,9,Fboys in the Hampshire town, in
OL,10,FNovember 2024, when she was 15.
OL,12,FThe offenders, who were 14 at the time
OL,13,Fand are now aged 15, went on to rape a
OL,14,Fsecond girl in January 2025,
OL,15,Fencouraged by a third boy now aged 14,
OL,16,Fwith all three later convicted of
OL,17,Fmultiple rape and indecent image
OL,18,Foffences.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782895707
OL,3,CRape victim says she 'will never be
OL,4,Cthe same' ahead of sentence review
OL,6,FBut they were spared custody for the
OL,7,Foffences in May, with the Attorney
OL,8,FGeneral Lord Hermer referring the
OL,9,Fsentences to the Court of Appeal as
OL,10,F"unduly lenient" days later following
OL,11,Fpublic outcry.
OL,13,FThe bid to have the sentences
OL,14,Fincreased is set to be heard on
OL,15,FWednesday.
OL,17,FIn a statement to the Press
OL,18,FAssociation ahead of the hearing,
OL,19,FJazmine said the trial at Southampton
OL,20,FCrown Court was "traumatising".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782895707
OL,3,CRape victim says she 'will never be
OL,4,Cthe same' ahead of sentence review
OL,6,FShe said: "I feel like I am carrying
OL,7,Fwhat happened every day. I wake up
OL,8,Fwith it, I go to school with it, I try
OL,9,Fto sit exams with it, and I go to
OL,10,Fsleep with it. It is always there. I
OL,11,Fcannot just switch it off. I cannot
OL,12,Fjust move on.
OL,14,F"The trial was horrific. It was not
OL,15,Fjust difficult; it was traumatising.
OL,16,FIt made me relive what happened again
OL,17,Fand again.
OL,19,F"The trial lasted more than five-and-a-
OL,20,Fhalf weeks, and I had to go through
OL,21,Fgiving evidence.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782895707
OL,3,CRape victim says she 'will never be
OL,4,Cthe same' ahead of sentence review
OL,6,F"When I gave evidence, I was
OL,7,Fquestioned in detail about what I
OL,8,Fapparently did. I was asked about the
OL,9,Fdetails of what happened."
OL,11,FShe continued: "It was implied that I
OL,12,Fwanted it. It was implied that I was
OL,13,Fexperienced in what I was doing. It
OL,14,Fwas implied that I had chosen it or
OL,15,Ftaken part in it.
OL,17,F"I cannot explain how humiliating and
OL,18,Fpainful that was. I was 15 years old.
OL,19,FI am a child who has been raped. I
OL,20,Ffelt like I was being treated like I
OL,21,Fhad done something wrong.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782895707
OL,3,CRape victim says she 'will never be
OL,4,Cthe same' ahead of sentence review
OL,6,F"The hardest part was being accused of
OL,7,Flying. I knew I was telling the truth.
OL,8,FI knew what had happened to me.
OL,10,F"I tried so hard to do my best whilst
OL,11,Ftalking about something which has left
OL,12,Fme with such lasting pain. That broke
OL,13,Fsomething inside me.
OL,15,F"What happened to me has left me
OL,16,Fharmed so severely that I do not think
OL,17,FI will ever be the same."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/14
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
